name: ecommerce_webServices
description: Microservices based E-Commerce web application. Product Catalog Service with CRUD operations. Tools & Frameworks - Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, Rest Template, MVC Pattern.

name: nx-mono
description: Extendible and flexible base for a monorepository project on NX build system with dynamic module federation of microservices. Shell is an Angular application.

name: Food-Delivery-App
description: This project aims to create a comprehensive Food Delivery Web Application employing Microservice Architecture (with Nest.js, GraphQL, Next.js). Separate applications will be built for Admin, User, Restaurant Owner, and Delivery Man.

name: digital-bank
description: The Digital Bank project is a microservices-based application designed to provide a comprehensive banking solution. Built using Spring Boot, it consists of several services.

name: Stack-OverFlow-2.0
description: This project is a basic implementation of a Stack Overflow-like system built first as a monolithic web-based application and later broken down into microservices. The main goal of this project is to demonstrate the transition from a monolithic architecture to a microservices architecture.

name: Distributed-Tracing-with-OpenTelemetry-Jaegar-with-Daemonset-Pattern
description: This project is a simple Microservices application providing a REST API to hit at its endpoints. The application communicates with each other and utilises OpenTelemetry tracing to send trace data to a distributed tracing backend via an OpenTelemetry Collector.

name: user
description: Converse: A Chat Application using microservices architecture with grpc protocol for service to service communication.; Encryption and Decryption of Chat Messages; Web Sockets for real time communication and Angular Frontend along with Mysql for user profile storage and MongoDB for message storage.. This is User Microservice of the Converse App.

name: SpringJourney
description: This Spring Boot journey covers essential topics from beginner to advanced levels, including setting up applications, dependency injection, data access with JPA & Hibernate, Spring Security, building REST APIs, microservices, testing, deployment, and advanced features like caching, WebSockets, and distributed tracing.

name: micro-services-tutorial
description: This project demonstrates the principles of microservices architecture, utilizing Spring Boot for backend services. It includes user and role management services, integrated with Eureka for service discovery and Zipkin for distributed tracing. Perfect for learning how to build scalable and maintainable applications!.
